      <trans-unit id="15411" identifier="e088018b68753988a5e9bb3b7e4f23a4">
        <source>To find out if a number is even or odd, use the “mod” operation to find the remainder after dividing that number by two.</source>
        <target>crwdns15411:0crwdne15411:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15412" identifier="dd57e93b56626c11289fcf749906711a">
        <source>If the remainder is zero the number is even (the &lt;code&gt;scratch:() mod ()&lt;/code&gt; operation under “Operators” script returns the remainder from division of two numbers.</source>
        <target>crwdns15412:0crwdne15412:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15413" identifier="ed522c033469c6bcca68ace1a50aaf7e">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:(17) mod (3) // 2&lt;/code&gt;)</source>
        <target>crwdns15413:0crwdne15413:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li</note>
      </trans-unit>
